Print an mcgf object.

Source: R/print.mcgf.R
print.mcgf.Rd

Print an mcgf object.

Usage

# S3 method for mcgf
print(x, attr = ".Data", ...)

Arguments

x

An mcgf object.

attr

Attribute to be printed.

...

Optional arguments to print methods.

Value

No return value, called for side effects.

Examples

data(sim1)
sim1_mcgf <- mcgf(sim1$data, dists = sim1$dists)
#> `time` is not provided, assuming rows are equally spaced temporally.
print(sim1_mcgf, "dists")
